<p>
The horizontal <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/FunctionCentroid.ht=
ml">function centroids</a> of a convolution
add
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/Convolution/NumberedEquation4.svg" class=3D"numberedequation"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"130" height=
=3D"23" alt=3D" &lt;t&gt;_(f*g)=3D&lt;t&gt;_f+&lt;t&gt;_g, "></td><td align=
=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn18" class=3D"eqnum">
(18)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
and provided that either <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/e=
quations/Convolution/Inline69.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-hei=
ght:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"12" height=3D"21" alt=3D"f">
 or <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Convolution/=
Inline70.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:10=
0%" border=3D"0" width=3D"10" height=3D"21" alt=3D"g"> has its <a href=3D"h=
ttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/FunctionCentroid.html">function
 centroids</a> at its origin, the <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/=
Variance.html">variances</a> do as well
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/Convolution/NumberedEquation5.svg" class=3D"numberedequation"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"141" height=
=3D"27" alt=3D" &lt;t^2&gt;_(f*g)=3D&lt;t^2&gt;_f+&lt;t^2&gt;_g "></td><td =
align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn19" class=3D"eqnum">
(19)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
(Bracewell 1965, p.&nbsp;142), where
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/Convolution/NumberedEquation6.svg" class=3D"numberedequation"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"148" height=
=3D"54" alt=3D" &lt;t^n&gt;_f=3D(int_(-infty)^inftyt^nf(t)dt)/(int_(-infty)=
^inftyf(t)dt). "></td><td align=3D"right" width=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn20" class=3D"eqnum">
(20)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
There is also a definition of the convolution which arises in probability t=
heory and is given by
</p>
<div>
<table summary=3D"" width=3D"100%" align=3D"center" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0" style=3D"padding-left: 50px">
<tbody><tr><td align=3D"left"><img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/ima=
ges/equations/Convolution/NumberedEquation7.svg" class=3D"numberedequation"=
 style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"217" height=
=3D"38" alt=3D" F(t)*G(t)=3DintF(t-x)dG(x), "></td><td align=3D"right" widt=
h=3D"3">
<div id=3D"eqn21" class=3D"eqnum">
(21)
</div>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<p>
where <img src=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/images/equations/Convolutio=
n/Inline71.svg" class=3D"inlineformula" style=3D"max-height:100%;max-width:=
100%" border=3D"0" width=3D"123" height=3D"25" alt=3D"intF(t-x)dG(x)">
 is a <a href=3D"https://mathworld.wolfram.com/StieltjesIntegral.html">Stie=
ltjes integral</a>.
</p>
